---
import bars from '/assets/bars.svg'
import blueDotGrid from '/assets/bluedot_grid.svg'
import rockyCloud from '/assets/rocky_cloud.svg'
import rightArrowPointer from '/assets/right_arrow_pointer.svg'
import grarGrid from '/assets/gray_grid.png'
import shield from '/assets/shield.svg'
import monitor from '/assets/monitor.svg'
import questionMark from '/assets/question_mark.svg'
import speedometer from '/assets/speedometer.svg'
import cloud from '/assets/cloud.svg'
import consolePic from '/assets/console_pic.svg'
import check from '/assets/check.svg'


// import { WebNavBar } from './components/WebNavBar'
// import { WebFooter } from './components/WebFooter'
import SiteHeader from './SiteHeader.astro'

import { Icon } from 'astro-icon'

---

<div class="home min-h-screen font-raleway relative">
  <!-- <WebNavBar showHero={true} /> -->
  <SiteHeader />

  <div class="grid place-items-center h-screen">

    <div class="flex items-start justify-start mt-20 z-20">
      <div class="flex flex-col pl-4">
        <p class="text-3xl text-gray-600 ">
        <span class='leading-loose font-bold text-4xl text-teal-600 border-teal-600 border-b-4'>
          All the tools </span> &nbsp; you need to explore and monitor APIs
          <br> <span class="font-semibold text-teal-600">round the clock and across the continents</span>
        </p>
        <p class="mt-12 w-3/5 text-gray-600 mb-4 text-xl">
          Monitor your APIs and Web sites seemlessly round the clock. Get notified on your favourite channel when behaviour is not as expected
        </p>
        <div class="flex mt-12 items-begin pl-4">
          <a href="/console/signup">
            <button class="bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-800 w-56 rounded-full p-2 text-white text-xl ">
              Start now - <span class="text-base">It's free</span>
            </button>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    
    <div class="mt-16 grid grid-cols-2 grid-rows-2 gap-10">
      {/*  Dashboard  */}
      <div class="flex items-start">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex align-middle items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-blue-100 w-10 h-10">
          <img class="w-6 h-6" src={bars} />
        </div>
        <div class="ml-4 flex flex-col items-begin justify-start text-xl">
          <p class="text-2xl text-blue-600 mb-2">Powerful API Explorer and Monitor</p>
          <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-2">
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Explore REST APIs with ease</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Setup Monitors at regular intervals</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Choose Test Criteria</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Get notified wherever you are</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Supports JSON, XML, HTML, Text inputs </span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Authenticate using Basic, Bearer and OAuth</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      

      <div class="flex items-start">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex align-middle items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-green-100 w-10 h-10">
          <img class="w-6 h-6" src={shield} />
        </div>
        <div class="ml-4 flex flex-col items-begin justify-start text-xl">
          <p class="text-2xl text-green-600 mb-2">Analytics</p>
          <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-2">
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Uptime for any period to understand SLA</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Latency metrics with connection timings</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Gain insights by measuring in any time period</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Dig deep into errors</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      {/*  Speed  */}
      <div class="flex items-start">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex align-middle items-center rounded-full bg-green-100 w-10 h-10">
          <img class="w-6 h-6" src={speedometer} />
        </div>
        <div class="ml-4 flex flex-col items-begin justify-start text-xl">
          <p class="text-2xl text-green-600 mb-2">Geographic Locations</p>
          <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-2">
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Choose from world wide locations closer to your customers</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Cover all continents and important cities</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Optional Private Locations</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="flex items-start">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex align-middle items-center rounded-full bg-green-100 w-10 h-10">
          <img class="w-6 h-6" src={monitor} />
        </div>
        <div class="ml-4 flex flex-col items-begin justify-start text-xl">
          <p class="text-2xl text-red-600 mb-2">Security</p>
          <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-2">
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Sharebale Environments</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Keep tabs on SSL certificate expiration</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Encryption at Rest</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center justify-start">
              <Icon name="fe:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" /> 
              <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">Encryption during Transit</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      
    </div>

    <div class="flex items-center justify-center">
      {/* showcase rectangle grid */}
      <div class="relative w-1/2 h-64 rounded-xl bg-blue-400 -ml-32 z-20">
        {/* white dots */}
        <img
          class="absolute mt-8 mr-8 top-0 right-0"
          src="../assets/whitedots_grid.png"
        />
        
      </div>
      <div class="mt-32 bg-gray-200 w-2/3 h-64 z-0 flex items-center justify-center">
        <div class="flex flex-col items-start content-start w-1/3">
          <p class="text-2xl">
            About <span class="font-semibold">Product</span>
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">
            TLS secured connections with public key server identity. Password
            based user identity and ACL based topic authorizations
          </p>
          <a href="/docs/promqtt.html">
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-red-600">
              <img class="inline" src={rightArrowPointer} /> Learn more
            </p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {/* cloud edu*/}
    <div class="relative mt-64 w-2/3 h-64 mx-auto">
      <img class="absolute z-0" src={cloud} />
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center relative z-20 pt-8">
        <img src={blueDotGrid} />
        <img class="ml-6" src={questionMark} />
        <p class="ml-6 text-xl text-gray-600">
          New to <span class="font-semibold">MQTT Brokers?</span>
          <br />
          <br />
          <span>
            MQTT is the protocol of choice for connecting IoT devices to the
            internet. It has a number of advantages compared to HTTP in
            operating in a constrained environment and efficiently using
            limited bandwidth.
          </span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-start">
      <div class="mx-auto flex items-center justify-start mt-24 w-1/2 h-16 bg-gray-200">
        <p class="ml-4">What is MQTT?</p>
      </div>
      <p class="ml-12 mt-4 w-2/5 text-sm text-gray-600">
        MQTT is the protocol of choice for connecting IoT devices to the
        internet. It has a number of advantages compared to HTTP in operating
        in a onstrained environment and efficiently using limited bandwidth.
        <br />
        <br />
        The protocol is designed by IBM researchers for connecting small
        devices to the internet. All messages are binary and use a small
        message header. When compared to HTTP, MQTT messages are much smaller.
        It is also designed towards maintaining long lived persistent
        connections unlike HTTP, which helps in real time bidirectional
        communication. It also amortizes expensive but mandatory handshake in
        establishing secure connections.
      </p>
    </div>
    <!-- <div class="mt-12">
      <WebFooter></WebFooter>
    </div> -->
  </div>
</div>  

<style>
.bg-gradient-callout {
  background-image: linear-gradient(114deg, #fe4272 35%, #f98b4c 83%);
}
</style>